reviewText: "La mujer que no tuvo infancia"  is  one of the best acted, directed, and written comedies I ever saw. Pedro Armendariz and Libertad Lamarque, in addition to being fine actors, also have crystal clear diction. I had one Spanish class in community college, before seeing this film, and was able to follow 90% of the dialogue.
This movie is a GEM!!!!!  Lamarque is one of the greatest actresses in Latin America.  She is multi-faceted!  She sings like an angel and Cri Cri's songs are a blessing!!!
